verses.text: Then Jacob went on his journey , and came into the land of the people of the east.\f + \fr 29.1 \ft went…: Heb. lift up his feet\f*\f + \fr 29.1 \ft people: Heb. children\f*

And he looked , and behold a well in the field , and, lo, there \add were\add* three flocks of sheep lying by it; for out of that well they watered the flocks : and a great stone \add was\add* upon the well’s mouth.
And thither were all the flocks gathered : and they rolled the stone from the well’s mouth , and watered the sheep , and put the stone again upon the well’s mouth in his place.
And Jacob said unto them, My brethren , whence \add be\add* ye? And they said , Of Haran \add are\add* we.
And he said unto them, Know ye Laban the son of Nahor ? And they said , We know \add him\add*.
And he said unto them, \add Is\add* he well ? And they said , \add He is\add* well : and, behold, Rachel his daughter cometh with the sheep.\f + \fr 29.6 \ft Is he…: Heb. Is there peace to him?\f*

And he said , Lo , \add it is\add* yet high day , neither \add is it\add* time that the cattle should be gathered together : water ye the sheep , and go \add and\add* feed \add them\add*.\f + \fr 29.7 \ft it is…: Heb. yet the day is great\f*
And they said , We cannot , until all the flocks be gathered together , and \add till\add* they roll the stone from the well’s mouth ; then we water the sheep. \p
¶ And while he yet spake with them, Rachel came with her father’s sheep : for she kept them.

And it came to pass, when Jacob saw Rachel the daughter of Laban his mother’s brother , and the sheep of Laban his mother’s brother , that Jacob went near , and rolled the stone from the well’s mouth , and watered the flock of Laban his mother’s brother.
And Jacob kissed Rachel , and lifted up his voice , and wept.
And Jacob told Rachel that he \add was\add* her father’s brother , and that he \add was\add* Rebekah’s son : and she ran and told her father.

And it came to pass, when Laban heard the tidings of Jacob his sister’s son , that he ran to meet him, and embraced him, and kissed him, and brought him to his house. And he told Laban all these things.\f + \fr 29.13 \ft tidings: Heb. hearing\f*
And Laban said to him, Surely thou \add art\add* my bone and my flesh. And he abode with him the space of a month.\f + \fr 29.14 \ft the space…: Heb. a month of days\f* \p
¶ And Laban said unto Jacob , Because thou \add art\add* my brother , shouldest thou therefore serve me for nought ? tell me, what \add shall\add* thy wages \add be\add*?
And Laban had two daughters : the name of the elder \add was\add* Leah , and the name of the younger \add was\add* Rachel.
Leah \add was\add* tender eyed ; but Rachel was beautiful and well favoured.
And Jacob loved Rachel ; and said , I will serve thee seven years for Rachel thy younger daughter.
And Laban said , \add It is\add* better that I give her to thee, than that I should give her to another man : abide with me.
And Jacob served seven years for Rachel ; and they seemed unto him \add but\add* a few days , for the love he had to her. \p
¶ And Jacob said unto Laban , Give \add me\add* my wife , for my days are fulfilled , that I may go in unto her.
And Laban gathered together all the men of the place , and made a feast.
And it came to pass in the evening , that he took Leah his daughter , and brought her to him; and he went in unto her.
And Laban gave unto his daughter Leah Zilpah his maid \add for\add* an handmaid.

And it came to pass, that in the morning , behold, it \add was\add* Leah : and he said to Laban , What \add is\add* this thou hast done unto me? did not I serve with thee for Rachel ? wherefore then hast thou beguiled me?
And Laban said , It must not be so done in our country , to give the younger before the firstborn.\f + \fr 29.26 \ft country: Heb. place\f*
Fulfil her week , and we will give thee this also for the service which thou shalt serve with me yet seven other years.
And Jacob did so, and fulfilled her week : and he gave him Rachel his daughter to wife also.
And Laban gave to Rachel his daughter Bilhah his handmaid to be her maid.
And he went in also unto Rachel , and he loved also Rachel more than Leah , and served with him yet seven other years. \p
¶ And when the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* saw that Leah \add was\add* hated , he opened her womb : but Rachel \add was\add* barren.

And Leah conceived , and bare a son , and she called his name Reuben : for she said , Surely the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath looked upon my affliction ; now therefore my husband will love me.\f + \fr 29.32 \ft Reuben: that is, See a son\f*

And she conceived again, and bare a son ; and said , Because the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath heard that I \add was\add* hated , he hath therefore given me this \add son\add* also: and she called his name Simeon.\f + \fr 29.33 \ft Simeon: that is, Hearing\f*

And she conceived again , and bare a son ; and said , Now this time will my husband be joined unto me, because I have born him three sons : therefore was his name called Levi.\f + \fr 29.34 \ft Levi: that is, Joined\f*

And she conceived again, and bare a son : and she said , Now will I praise the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: therefore she called his name Judah ; and left bearing.\f + \fr 29.35 \ft Judah: that is, Praise\f*\f + \fr 29.35 \ft left…: Heb. stood from bearing\f*
